02/06/2006
VISEGRAD, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A former Bosnian Serb policeman suspected of war crimes was arrested in Visegrad on Thursday (1 June), according to an announcement from the Eastern Sarajevo Public Security Centre. Borislav Berjan, 56, was apprehended at the Sarajevo Cantonal Court on charges of genocide and crimes committed against prisoners of war. Separately Thursday, the Eastern Sarajevo police detained Bosnian Serbs Momir Pandurevic and Djoka Staka, on the basis of a warrant issued by the Sarajevo Cantonal Court. (PBS BiH, RTRS, Pincom.info - 01/06/06)
